# RHOAI Version Compatibility

## Supported Versions

| Version | Channel Options | Use Case |
|---------|-----------------|----------|
| RHOAI 3.4 | `fast-3.x`, `stable-3.4` | Latest — MaaS (core GA, some sub-features TP), NeMo Guardrails (GA), AutoML/AutoRAG (TP) |
| RHOAI 3.3 | `fast-3.x`, `stable-3.3` | Stable — MaaS (TP), llm-d (GA), Llama Stack 0.4.2 |
| RHOAI 3.2 | `fast-3.x`, `stable-3.2` | Production with GenAI, MaaS |
| RHOAI 2.25 | `stable` | Workshops, demos |
| RHOAI 2.22, 2.19 | `stable-X.Y` | Legacy |

Channels vary by cluster. Check with:
```bash
oc get packagemanifest rhods-operator -n openshift-marketplace -o jsonpath='{.status.channels[*].name}'
```

## RHOAI 3.4 Changes (vs 3.3)

### GA Promotions
- **MaaS (Models-as-a-Service)** — Core platform now GA (subscriptions, API keys, llm-d serving). Sub-features still TP: external OIDC auth, vLLM runtime, observability dashboard, external model egress
- **NeMo Guardrails** — Now GA with `/v1/guardrails/checks` endpoint, regex rails, multi-replica, OpenTelemetry
- **MLServer ServingRuntime** — Now GA for scikit-learn, XGBoost, LightGBM, ONNX
- **MLflow Operator** — Now an official managed DSC component (`mlflowoperator`); dashboard flag deprecated

### New Features (Technology Preview)
- **AutoML** — Automated ML model training via Kubeflow Pipelines + AutoGluon
- **AutoRAG** — Automated RAG optimization
- **vLLM runtime for MaaS** — Enable via `vLLMDeploymentOnMaaS` dashboard flag
- **External OIDC auth for MaaS** — Enterprise identity provider integration
- **MaaS observability dashboard** — Usage metrics, token tracking, CSV export
- **External model egress** — Route to OpenAI, Anthropic etc. via inference gateway
- **Workload Variant Autoscaler (WVA)** — Inference-aware autoscaling for llm-d
- **Priority-based flow control** — Mixed workload scheduling for llm-d
- **Gateway discovery** — Self-service Gateway selection for llm-d
- **EvalHub** — Evaluation Stack UI + SDK/CLI for model evaluation
- **Text embedding models** — Dedicated embedding models in Model Catalog
- **Artifact signing** — Cryptographic signing/verification for model registry

### Enhancements
- **llm-d** — Prometheus metrics, simplified scheduler via `endpointPickerConfig`, vLLM args via `args` field
- **Model Registry** — OCI-compliant storage, PostgreSQL backend, default database for testing
- **Workbench images** — Default to Red Hat Python index (not PyPI)
- **Llama Stack 0.6.0** — Responses API (TP), Connectors, Conversations API, Garak eval
- **Trainer** — JIT checkpointing, S3 storage for checkpoints

## RHOAI 3.3 Changes (vs 3.2)

- **Kubeflow Trainer v2** — GA, requires JobSet operator, use `trainer` not `trainingoperator`
- **MLServer ServingRuntime** — Tech Preview for scikit-learn, XGBoost
- **Llama Stack 0.4.2** — OpenAI-compatible RAG annotations
- **MaaS Zero-Touch** — via `modelsAsService` in DSC
- **NVIDIA NIM** — `kserve.nim.managementState: Managed`
- **MLflow Operator** — experiment tracking
- **Dashboard URL** — `data-science-gateway.apps.<cluster>` (was `rhods-dashboard`)
- **CodeFlare removed** — use KubeRay directly
- **Resource naming** — `data-science-` prefix
- **Feature Store** — stricter label/restAPI requirements for dashboard visibility

